interactions.flavorLineOne:
Nimbus claps you on the back in greeting. After everything that's happened, you are a true ally of Neomuna and welcome in the city anytime.

"We may not be the hottest tourist spot in the system," they quip, looking out at the smoldering skyline, "but we'll take all the help we can get."

There's an ironic twist to the Cloud Strider's mouth, but it can't cover up the worry in their eyes. "Osiris filled me in on everything else that's happened. The Witness created some kind of portal in your Traveler and went through it, right? If it's rejecting all probes… then forget about getting people through it."

"I can't claim we've got the answers, but we're all in this together, right? Humanity's gotta help each other, Neptune or Earth. Neomuna's role in this war isn't over by a long shot. While everyone figures out what's next, could use your help holding the line here. The less gets by us, the less comes at you later.  And when we do know what's next, Neomuna's got your back. It's our galaxy too."

"…Oh, wait. This came for you, I think?" Nimbus says, holding up what appears to be a ceremonial scepter of Awoken origin.

"Don't ask me," they shrug. "It showed up alongside that clunky piece of technology over there." 

Nimbus gestures to a nearby Vanguard holoprojector. Its boxy terran design is conspicuously awkward amidst the sleek architecture of Neomuna. 

"Those things just popped out of a swirling purple portal—and that's not even close to the weirdest thing that's happened here recently."

You take the scepter and notice the lights of the holoprojector flashing with an urgent message…

This quest begins the Season of Defiance campaign.
As a reward for completing the Legendary campaign, you have received Strand Meditations to help in the battles to come.
"Been seeing a few more hopeful faces around lately. Knowing you're here to help really keeps morale up, you know? The people of Neomuna appreciate it, and so do I." —Nimbus

Nimbus takes the Vex compass and Seed of Silver Wings off your hands. They don't mention Osiris insisting they stay behind, though their dampened enthusiasm says it all. 

As they recheck Rohan's notes, they explain the passkey's design. The compass, tuned to the shifting unpredictability of the Nexus, should bring you right to the Black Garden's door. 

There, the Seed of Silver Wings, refractive with the Garden's fluctuating DNA, should allow you to enter as if you belong.

Nimbus presses their Cloud Strider core. A whirl of nanites fly out, welding the components together. 

As they work, Nimbus points out a name in Rohan's notes: the Conceptual Mind.

This is the architect Rohan saw building the Black Heart 10 years ago. It's also your best chance at unlocking the Veil, following the Witness, and bringing a worthy end to Rohan's unfinished business.

They hand over the finished passkey and wish you good luck.

Head to In.Gress to launch the "What Remains" mission.

Nimbus introduces themself as the "Rookie Cloud Strider" in Neomuna. Nimbus, their superior, Rohan, and the long line of Cloud Striders who came before them have been keeping the city and its citizens safe for a long time sans-Guardians. Nimbus isn't sure what Guardians can bring to the table now, but it seems Neomuna and the Vanguard have similar enemies. It can't hurt to work together, right?

Complete the mission "Under Siege" in Neomuna.

"The Witness is still out there," Nimbus says, looking out across the city with uncharacteristic seriousness, "but we're not going down without a fight. What we've done here will help us in the days to come. I'm sure of it."

Their smile returns in full force, and they wink at you. "So go on, Guardian! Put some of these shiny, explosive new toys to use."

As a reward for completing the Legendary campaign, you have received powerful gear to help in the battles to come.

Nimbus beams as you approach, clapping you on the shoulder. "Well, well, well! If it isn't the hero of the hour!" 

Not even the remaining threats to the city can dim their enthusiasm, it seems. Their smile turns wry as they look out over Neomuna.

"Job's not done yet. But it's easier to shoulder the burden with a helping hand. And I'm glad it's yours."

You have completed the Legendary campaign. Please select your reward.

"Y'know, word in the CloudArk is, there's someone from Earth running around the city. Except they aren't a Warlord trying to take over, they're a Guardian here to help and kick butt. How about that, huh?" —Nimbus
"You're keeping up great, Guardian! Between us, the Vex and the Shadow Legion don't stand a chance. Neomuna's staying safe as long as we have anything to say about it." —Nimbus

Calus beat us to the Veil and secured it on behalf of the Witness. Luckily, its containment infrastructure should delay their efforts, at least for a little while. Based on Ghost's strange experience, it appears Calus intends to use a device called the Radial Mast to link the Veil with the Traveler.

Whatever the Witness wants, this can't be good. With Calus's forces focused on the Veil containment, Osiris wants us to hit Calus's fortress directly and take out this Radial Mast before it is moved closer to the Veil. Even despite Rohan's concerns.

Nimbus recommends you check in with Rohan and Osiris at the Hall of Heroes before moving on to mission "Downfall."

You power-cycled the CloudArk—the tech built off the Veil that keeps all Neomuni citizens linked in their virtual infrastructure. With the CloudArk back online, they'll be able to contribute more to resisting Calus's assault on their city. Your recent success with Strand has Osiris and Nimbus thinking it's worth exploring further, as another potential advantage over Calus. You're still not ready for a head-on assault but, maybe with Strand, you can be. 

After a pleasant chat with Osiris, Nimbus was reminded of a place that you and the Old Bird might find useful for mastering Strand. Before they hand you the coordinates, they take a moment to tell you just how much you amaze them. It took Rohan a while to give Nimbus their first compliment on the job, and they made a promise that they'd do it differently when they took over. The old man might think compliments go to your head, but Nimbus sees nothing but good in appreciating people when they deserve it.

Nimbus recommends you check in with Rohan and Osiris at the Hall of Heroes before moving on to mission "On The Verge."

Death is part of a Cloud Strider's lot. Nimbus knows this, but that doesn't make Rohan's early exit any easier to accept. 

Still, he made every moment count; by destroying the Radial Mast, Rohan wrecked the Witness's plan for creating a link with the Veil.

But that doesn't mean the war is over. Calus is sure to retaliate—and it looks like his sights are set on the CloudArk. 

There's no time to mourn now. The best way to honor Rohan is to get Neomuna's defense systems up and running again.

You might check in with Osiris and Caiatl in the Hall of Heroes before jumping back into the fray. 

Complete the strike "HyperNet Current" in Neomuna.

Nimbus congratulates you on the progress you've made with Strand. They council on your next steps, saying that now is probably the best time for you and Osiris to try to master the element. Nimbus also thinks Rohan would agree.

As a sign of the trust you have built together, Nimbus refers to themself with their true name: Cloud Strider Dara Danu. They thought you should know.

Complete the mission "Headlong" in Neomuna.

Nimbus admits they weren't as settled with Rohan's death as they thought they were. Cloud Striders are trained to accept death as part of the flow. To Nimbus, that meant pushing through the pain, trying to outrun their grief. 

Seeing Rohan's gun in the Black Garden forced them to stop and realize just how much they missed him. 

Nimbus thanks you for seeing the mission through. With the Conceptual Mind's memory core, the odds of unlocking the Veil and following the Witness have shot up. 

Nimbus promises to deliver the memory core so Osiris and Neomuna's researchers can start decrypting it. 

There's just one stop Nimbus has to make first.

Go to the Hall of Heroes to honor those who cut their years short for the sake of humanity.

Nimbus is bummed about the outcome of the last mission—they were really rooting for you. They sympathize by recounting Rohan's little catchphrase for such an occasion: "Headlong and empty-handed," explaining that it's okay to stop trying to do it all yourself; we're in this together. We'll fix this. 

Whatever the Witness wants from the Veil clearly involves using the Radial Mast to create some sort of… link? So the threat remains high. But right now, the CloudArk—Neomuna's virtual infrastructure built on the Veil's power—needs our help. "I'm sure you've seen the virtual citizens milling about the city. You see… nah, you know what, I'll explain details on the way. Point is, to protect the Veil, we need to protect the CloudArk." Your direct assault on Calus failed. Time to try a different approach.

Nimbus recommends you check in with Rohan and Osiris at the Hall of Heroes before moving on to mission "Breakneck."

All Nimbus had to hear was "Strand weapon" for them to hop on board with your project. "What a great idea! Why didn't we think of this sooner?" they practically shout in enthusiasm. 

They switch to brainstorming mode. "Hm. A weapon that harnesses the Veil's energy… can't be made outta your everyday stuff. At the very least, you'll need the same grade materials as the Veil Containment." 

The Cloud Strider perks up. "Actually, you could just retrofit some of the Irkalla Institute's old equipment. I bet their atmospheric spectrometers are chock full of Strand energy!"

Search Veil Containment for an atmospheric Veil spectrometer.

"Bluejay, huh? That's a heck of a story." Nimbus grins. "Jain had serious problems with authority. Makes me look like an Academy drill instructor by comparison. Big brain, though, and an even bigger heart. Once he learned to actually listen to others, he went from public enemy to public hero. Eventually became a Cloud Strider."

"The Cloud Striders maintain the original sim space he built way back when. It's technically in the VexNet, so we use it like a listening post. Problem is, with everything going on, it's full of Vex. Locked with a quadrinomial encryption sequence too. Nasty stuff. You'd need a Polymorphic Engine to crack it. And a ton of their Shellcode samples."

They pat you on the shoulder. "This is the part where I tell you to stay away. 'It's too dangerous.' But neither of us would believe it coming from me."

Destroy Vex and gather their Shellcode Fragments to continue bonding with this legacy.

Nimbus admits to leaving the induction ceremony early; it doesn't feel right when Neomuna is still overrun and the Witness is at large. 

If you ask them, a better way to honor Rohan's legacy would be to finish his unfinished business and find the Vex's copycat Veil.

Apparently, early in his training, Rohan stumbled on the Vex building what he believed was a copy of the Veil. Convinced this was a threat, he spent the rest of his career trying to retrace his steps through the Nexus. Nimbus believes Rohan succeeded right before the Shadow Legion's invasion. 

They ask for your help finding Rohan's notes, hidden all around the city in encrypted data packets. To recover the data, you will need cipher qubits, which can be collected from the Vex.

Defeat Vex in Neomuna to collect qubits and recover Rohan's data packets.

Nimbus takes the Vex compass and Seed of Silver Wings off your hands. They don't mention Osiris insisting they stay behind, though their dampened enthusiasm says it all. 

As they recheck Rohan's notes, they explain the passkey's design. The compass, tuned to the shifting unpredictability of the Nexus, should bring you right to the Black Garden's door. 

There, the Seed of Silver Wings, refractive with the Garden's fluctuating DNA, should allow you to enter as if you belong.

Nimbus presses their Cloud Strider core. A whirl of nanites fly out, welding the components together. 

As they work, Nimbus points out a name in Rohan's notes: the Conceptual Mind.

This is the architect Rohan saw building the Black Heart 10 years ago. It's also your best chance at unlocking the Veil, following the Witness, and bringing a worthy end to Rohan's unfinished business.

They hand over the finished passkey and wish you good luck.

Head to In.Gress to launch the "What Remains" mission.
Dropped your Shellcode?

Nimbus introduces themself as the "Rookie Cloud Strider" in Neomuna. Nimbus, their superior, Rohan, and the long line of Cloud Striders who came before them have been keeping the city and its citizens safe for a long time sans-Guardians. Nimbus isn't sure what Guardians can bring to the table now, but it seems Neomuna and the Vanguard have similar enemies. It can't hurt to work together, right?

Complete the mission "Under Siege" in Neomuna.

Calus is gone.

With an uncharacteristically heavy voice, Nimbus confides they aren't sure what victory looks like going forward, but they're not going to let that undercut the relief that their home and their people are safe.

It feels weird to not be "the rookie" anymore, they tell you; Rohan left big shoes to fill. Nimbus's voice takes a hopeful upturn: they'll get there someday.

They invite you to Rohan's induction ceremony into the Hall of Heroes, telling you Rohan would be honored if you attended.

Attend Rohan's Hall of Heroes induction.

Nimbus greets you with their usual enthusiasm. "Guardian! Listen, Osiris just got in touch. He says his data crawler uncovered all kinds of weird stuff."

Their smile becomes a little self-deprecating. "You're better at understanding ancient history and… what did the old bird call it? Paracausal studies? Something like that. The point is, I think you'll get more out of Osiris's data crawler than I will."

"Head back down there and take a look. And let me know if you find anything interesting."

While Nimbus supports going on the offense, they caution you not to forget the ordinary people caught in the crossfire.

The people of Neomuna are skeptical of Earth's Warlords, and they're caught between dual assaults from the Shadow Legion and Vex. Nimbus has some ideas for how you can tackle both problems at once.

Complete tasks to bolster the city's defenses and improve relations between Earth and Neomuna.

With Rohan gone, the weight of protecting Neomuna falls heaviest on Nimbus's shoulders. Their greeting lacks its usual cheer, but they rally enough to attempt a smile.

"Me? Aw, don't worry, I've got it all handled! But between you and me, the citizens could really use some hope right now. People will feel better knowing our allies have our backs."

Complete tasks to bolster the city's defenses and inspire the Neomuni people.

"Hey, Guardian! Thanks for coming down."

Nimbus is eager to get to work as they stand up, clapping their hands together.

"We've had some weird Vex activity going on across the city in the last couple weeks. When I sent the data to Osiris, he got all excited about it." Nimbus smirks. "You know how he gets."

Nimbus rolls their shoulders, ready for action. "Osiris thinks whatever the Vex are after has to do with the Veil, and he wants you to look into it; collect some data, see what they've been digging into." Nimbus sighs.

"Problem is, we don't have a lead on the Vex… but the Shadow Legion does. So we're gonna pay 'em a visit, bust a few heads, and figure out which Vex we need to target." Nimbus slaps a fist into their open palm.

"I'll be on overwatch," they eagerly explain, "and the old man will be in your ear the whole way." Then Nimbus raises their brow, motioning to the overlook's edge. 

"So, ready to roll?"

Complete bounties, patrols, public events, Lost Sectors, Terminal Overload runs, replayable campaign missions, Partition activities, secrets, and open chests in Neomuna to increase your Neomuna rank and earn rewards.
